The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during his visit to Japan. Pence emphasizes the strong alliance between the United States and Japan, particularly in the face of the North Korean threat. He reiterates the commitment of the United States to defend Japan and work with allies in the region to pressure North Korea to abandon its nuclear and ballistic missile programs. Pence also discusses the economic ties between the two countries, highlighting the importance of the partnership in generating growth and prosperity. He mentions the recent increase in Japanese investment in the United States and outlines the goals of the U.S.-Japan Economic Dialogue, which include seeking a common strategy on trade and investment, addressing fiscal and monetary issues, and promoting sectoral cooperation. Pence concludes by expressing confidence in the future of the U.S.-Japan relationship and the potential for both nations to achieve shared goals of job creation, economic growth, and prosperity.